title.rendered: Brisbane vs Hobart, Women’s Bash T20 League, Eliminator: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Team

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

Probable XI for Brisbane: Danielle Wyatt, Georgia Voll, Grace Harris, Amelia Kerr, Laura Harris, Ellie Johnston (wk), Jess Jonassen (c), Charli Knott, Nicola Hancock, Courtney Sippel, Jess Kerr

Probable XI for Hobart: Lizelle Lee (wk), Rachel Trenaman, Mignon du Preez, Elyse Villani (c), Heather Graham, Nicola Carey, Ruth Johnston, Naomi Stalenberg, Hayley Jensen, Amy Smith, Molly Strano

Pitch Report

Venue: Karen Rolton Oval, Adelaide

(Based on the last 3 games)

1st innings average score: 122

2nd innings average score: 115

Wickets per innings: 6

Type: Even contest between bat and ball.

Weather: Cloudy but no rain is forecast.

Wins

Batting 1st: 67%

Batting 2nd: 33%

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Other than Mignon du Preez, Hobart’s top order has looked brittle and uncertain.

Brisbane’s bowlers have been regularly striking, regardless of the conditions. 

Smart Picks

Amelia Kerr’s dual ability, coupled with her consistency, has ensured that her selection percentage hasn’t dropped below 93 in this tournament. Besides adding 243 runs, she has generated 190 points only through dismissals with the ball.

Mignon du Preez has been a part of the Ultimate Team in her last three outings, with scores of 50*, 75, and 38. She has also provided 9 bonus points by smashing as many sixes.

Nicola Hancock is the leading wicket-taker (22) for Brisbane. In her previous two outings against Hobart in this tournament, she picked up a four- and two-wicket haul.

On both occasions against Hobart this season, Laura Harris has made a huge impact in fantasy leagues with her blazing knocks (68 off 29) and (32 off 20). 109 colossal points in only two games is a testimony to her game-changing abilities.

In 10 out of 14 games, Jess Jonassen has been amongst the wickets. Overall, she has bagged 20 wickets in this edition. She has also collected 64 runs with the bat in her last three innings. Given the tricky wicket at Adelaide, she will have a big role to play.

Molly Strano has garnered 186 points for taking 18 wickets, including bonus points for a three- and four-for.

Lizelle Lee has made decent contributions with the bat by adding 99 runs in her last 5 games, although she has managed a mere dismissal.
